This paper deals with the problem of sparse regression with highly correlated predictors, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a new algorithm, the clustering removal algorithm (CRA), to address this problem. The paper also provides theoretical analysis and empirical results to support the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm. Given the focus on sparse regression and the use of linear algebra and probability theory, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.ST (Statistics), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
